    "body": "> The long-term idea is to move from uint8_t to std::byte everywhere?\r\n\r\nYes, in places where raw bytes are handled. Though, this is mostly a style question, so there is no rush or need to switch existing code. For example, #23438 updates serialize to use Spans, and updating to `std::byte` at the same time was \"free\".",
